msDesc.head: Ólafs saga Tryggvasonar, Vol. II; Iceland, s. XVII.

msItem.title: Ólafs saga Tryggvasonar, vol. II
msItem.note: In two volumes; vol. I: AM 56 fol.
msItem.incipit:
OLafur konungur for vmm veturinn eptir jól
inn til Þrandheims.

filiation.p: According to Árni Magnússon's title on the spine, the manuscript is a copy of Flateyarbók.

foliation.p: Contemporary pagination (765-1431), presumably by Árni Magnússon.
Foliated (384-717) by Kristian Kålund in red ink.

p.catchwords: From f. 392v catchwords on every tenth page occur.

condition.p: The last half of the manuscript has suffered due to exposure to humidity and fol. 623 has a tear.

layout.p: The text is written in one column with 17 to 23 lines per page. There are cathchwords. Spaces left blank for initials.

handNote.p: Written by Jón Erlendsson of Villingaholt.

physDesc.additions: Occasional marginalia and additions by Árni Magnússon.

binding.p:
Binding from 1911; 315 215 85 . Half-binding with a parchment spine. The boards are covered with glossy marbled paper. The spine is from when Árni Magnússon collected the manuscripts. Árni Magnússon wrote: Olafs Saga Tryggvas.
ur Flateyiarbok.
Tom..II. pag. 765-1431. on the spine. On the upper pastedown, Kålund noted the date: 8. 8. 11..
The original parchment cover from 1700-1730 containing Petrus de Herental's Psalm commentaries was removed and transferred to Access 7e, hs. 123 (ff. 42, 46-47, 54, 56-57 and 78) in 1911.

origin.p: Written in Iceland in the seventeenth century.

custEvent.p: When the parchment cover was removed in 1911 the manuscript was provided with new flyleaves.
In 1999 the manuscript was dry cleaned and the spine was stabilised.
